article.description: Justin Kier had 14 points off the bench to carry George Mason to a 68-53 win over American on Saturday night.
article.headline: Kier scores 14 to lift George Mason past American 68-53
article.linkText: Kier scores 14 to lift George Mason past American 68-53
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- Justin Kier had 14 points off the bench to carry George Mason to a 68-53 win over American on Saturday night. Javon Greene had 13 points for George Mason (10-1), which earned its fifth consecutive victory. Xavier Johnson added 12 points and nine rebounds. Mark Gasperini had 13 points and nine rebounds for the Eagles (3-5). Sa'eed Nelson added six rebounds and Stacy Beckton Jr. grabbed another eight. George Mason plays Maryland-Baltimore County at home next Saturday. American faces Mount St. Mary's on the road next Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
